{
  "texts": [
    "Yet despite little outright objections (Bearne, 2025), the profession still lags in adoption of AI (Zhang et al., 2024).",
    "This paper explores the intersection of AI and SLP by drawing on insights from leading AI researchers and organizations.",
    "It examines how emerging tools are reshaping, and will continue to restructure the practice and science in SLP.",
    "The analysis is organized according to domains in the American Speech-Language-Hearing Association's (ASHA) Scope of Practice in Speech-Language Pathology (ASHA, 2016).",
    "In each domain, potential use cases, degrees of automation and augmentation, and broader implications for the profession are discussed."
  ]
}